Senator, how did you get the idea to run for president?
It's not about being a senator or president.
If everything was fine in our country, then I wouldn't run.
But I can no longer bear to see how it has been stolen in the last twenty years in our country, how thieves go unpunished, how taxes and the retirement age are raised.
I had no ambition to be a politician.
When I see something I don't like, I try to come up with a solution to change it.
And since I'm already 40 and running as an independent, the only chance I have of changing things is to run for senator or president.
He's already in the Senate, but soon after he's on his way to the presidency.
Aren't you turning your back on those people who voted for you?
I've always said that my candidacy for president depended on the results of the Senate elections.
